The party&#8217;s Enoch Godongwana says that recent events surrounding the ANC have been stressful. JOHANNESBURG - The African National Congress (ANC) head of economic transformation Enoch Godongwana says the Constitutional Court judgment on Nkandla, the state capture report and the loss of support at this year's polls have not only affected the country but has hurt the ANC. #ABSIP Godongwana Says he believes the ANC lost at this year&#39;s local gov elections.CMGodongwana was speaking at the 2016 Association of Black Securities and Investment Professionals (ABSIP) conference in Sandton on Tuesday.The conference is being held under the theme &quot;Economic Transformation for Social Change .#ABSIP Godongwana &quot;we have a political turmoil, it impacts a bit on economy&quot; CMGodongwana says the ANC is going through a painful period. They ve had very difficult circumstances. The Constitutional Court judgment, the state capture report and elections are painful and stressful for the nation and party. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)